# REST Client tests for this project
# Open this file in VS Code with the "REST Client" extension and click "Send Request" above each request.

# NOTE: The last request uses a variable `{{postId}}` which must be defined for the REST Client to run.
# Two ways to provide it:
# 1) Replace `{{postId}}` inline with a real id (quick and manual).
# 2) Create a workspace env file at `.vscode/rest-client.env.json` with a value for `postId`.
#    Example file is added to the repo: `.vscode/rest-client.env.json` (open and edit the value).

### List all posts
GET http://localhost:3000/posts/


### Open the "new post" form
GET http://localhost:3000/posts/new


### Create a new post (form-urlencoded)
POST http://localhost:3000/posts/new
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

title=Test+post+from+REST+Client&body=This+post+was+created+using+the+REST+Client+extension


### Create a new post (JSON)
POST http://localhost:3000/posts/new
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test JSON post",
  "body": "Created via JSON body. Server accepts JSON because express.json() is enabled."
}


